This paper is about Influence Maximization in Online Social Networks (OSNs), which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which focuses on the analysis and modeling of social networks and their impact on information diffusion. The second likely category is cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), which deals with the study of social and economic interactions among individuals, groups, and organizations. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is relevant because the paper proposes new algorithms for solving the Influence Maximization problem. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which is relevant because the paper proposes heuristic algorithms that can provide certain theoretical guarantees. The fifth likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which is relevant because the paper deals with the optimization of a complex system (i.e., an OSN) using computational methods.
